        "subtitle": "Includes both time-based and non-time-series synthetic network logs ",
        "description": "This dataset contains realistic synthetic network logs simulating both normal and malicious activity over a one-week period.\n\nIt includes two versions: \n1.  Time-series version (with timestamps): Ideal for sequential modeling, intrusion tracking, and temporal anomaly detection.\n2.  Non-time-series version (without timestamps): Suitable for standard classification or anomaly detection pipelines.\n\nInspiration:\nReal-world network intrusion logs are often private or restricted. This synthetic dataset provides a realistic yet accessible alternative for researchers, students, and ML engineers to build and benchmark intrusion detection systems.\n\n\n=== About this file ===\n\nAbout this file\nThis version removes the Timestamp column, making it ideal for:\nTraditional classification tasks\nAnomaly detection models that do not rely on time-based features\nLightweight or non-sequential ML pipelines\nLabels:\nIntrusion: Binary target (0 = Normal, 1 = Attack)\nScan_Type: Traffic type (Normal, PortScan, BotAttack)\n\n\n=== Columns & descriptions ===\n\nSource_IP: [no description]\nDestination_IP: [no description]\nPort: [no description]\nRequest_Type: [no description]\nProtocol: [no description]\nPayload_Size: [no description]\nUser_Agent: [no description]\nStatus: [no description]\nIntrusion: [no description]\nScan_Type: [no description]\n",
